WEBVTT

00:02.320 --> 00:03.913
MILES:
Previously on Revolution:

00:04.600 --> 00:07.718
BEN: It's gonna turn off
and it will never turn back on.

00:07.880 --> 00:09.473
What the hell is going on?

00:12.120 --> 00:14.919
Don't let anybody know you have it.
Keep it safe.

00:15.080 --> 00:16.673
Ben Matheson, come with us.

00:16.840 --> 00:19.150
DANNY: You can't take him.
- Stop! Back up!

00:19.360 --> 00:20.794
- No!
- Dad.

00:21.040 --> 00:23.714
Danny's gone.
My brother, Miles, is in Chicago.

00:23.880 --> 00:26.520
He can get Danny. You have to do this.

00:27.320 --> 00:29.470
Uncle Miles?
My brother's out there somewhere.

00:29.640 --> 00:31.199
It's my job to get him back.

00:31.920 --> 00:35.117
You wanna see him again, we're gonna go
against Monroe and his men.

00:35.280 --> 00:37.510
I gotta go get Nora.
You joined the rebels?

00:37.720 --> 00:39.119
Bring back the United States.

00:39.280 --> 00:41.794
You following us?
Who knows what he told Monroe.

00:41.960 --> 00:43.314
He's a spy, Charlie.

00:43.520 --> 00:46.034
MONROE: Your son, how do I know
where his loyalties lie?

00:46.200 --> 00:48.191
You have my word. I'll keep him in line.

00:49.520 --> 00:51.875
Let Danny go. I'll tell you everything.

00:52.040 --> 00:55.317
If you wanna turn the power back on,
it starts with these pendants.

00:55.480 --> 00:58.677
It's an amplifier. It slips on tanks, weapons.

00:58.880 --> 01:02.157
- You were in charge of the whole Militia?
- Yeah. I trained them.

01:03.880 --> 01:07.919
- Come back, I'll let your family live.
- I'm sorry I didn't kill you the first time.

01:09.160 --> 01:10.992
- Charlie?
- Mom?

01:11.160 --> 01:13.674
We're gonna find a way out.
We're gonna get your son.

01:13.880 --> 01:15.314
Danny?

01:15.480 --> 01:16.515
[GRUNTS]

01:38.120 --> 01:39.633
Go!

02:04.560 --> 02:06.039
In here.

03:00.040 --> 03:02.350
They're gonna look for the bodies.
We gotta go.

03:02.520 --> 03:05.990
- Where?
- As far away from Philly as we can get.

03:08.120 --> 03:10.111
[ALL COUGHING]

03:15.960 --> 03:17.280
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

03:29.040 --> 03:30.519
Sir?

03:33.440 --> 03:35.272
They've searched everywhere.

03:35.480 --> 03:39.474
They didn't find any remains.

03:40.640 --> 03:43.314
Is it possible there weren't any remains
to find?

03:44.560 --> 03:47.200
It's possible.

03:47.360 --> 03:50.591
But it's also Miles, so...

03:51.760 --> 03:53.273
Right.

03:54.440 --> 03:55.669
Miles.

03:57.360 --> 04:00.671
Who you let slip right past you
back at the prison.

04:01.560 --> 04:04.279
And escape with all his friends.

04:07.160 --> 04:09.879
He took advantage of you, Tom.

04:10.640 --> 04:13.200
That is a troubling weakness.

04:14.520 --> 04:15.954
I'm sorry, sir.

04:18.519 --> 04:19.839
Don't worry yourself.

04:21.760 --> 04:25.640
Miles doesn't matter.

04:25.800 --> 04:28.269
We have light, power.

04:28.440 --> 04:30.909
We have everything.

04:32.400 --> 04:35.153
It's time to let everyone know.
Starting with the rebels.

04:35.320 --> 04:38.438
You find me every rebel camp
in the republic. Every one.

04:38.600 --> 04:40.955
We send in the choppers,
wipe them from Earth.

04:41.120 --> 04:43.475
And once that irritation is done...

04:45.000 --> 04:46.877
...it's on to Georgia.

04:47.480 --> 04:49.630
Then the Plains Nation.

04:50.480 --> 04:52.437
Then California.

04:53.400 --> 04:56.711
It's all gonna be the Monroe Republic,
sea to shining sea.

04:57.520 --> 04:59.079
Yes, sir.

05:02.600 --> 05:04.273
And, Tom?

05:07.560 --> 05:10.473
If you do find Miles and he's alive?

05:13.880 --> 05:15.154
Kill him.

05:31.640 --> 05:33.916
- Cargo?
- Coming from the city morgue.

05:34.280 --> 05:37.033
- Let's take a look.
- Buddy, they're just corpses.

05:37.440 --> 05:41.035
We're on lockdown.
Checking everything coming out of Philly.

05:41.200 --> 05:43.669
- Why? What's going on?
GUARD: Escaped fugitives.

05:43.840 --> 05:46.309
We're looking for a couple of men.

05:47.760 --> 05:48.830
Some women too.

05:50.840 --> 05:52.592
Uh-huh.

05:56.400 --> 05:58.960
Look, we're just trying to do ourjob.

06:00.760 --> 06:02.319
Me too.

06:02.880 --> 06:04.678
Open them up.

06:13.920 --> 06:15.513
That one.

06:33.320 --> 06:34.469
[INHALES]

06:34.640 --> 06:35.960
[GRUNTS]

06:38.120 --> 06:40.191
Smell's killer, huh?

07:36.280 --> 07:40.160
So, Rachel, turns out you're not the mild
mannered housewife I thought you were.

07:40.320 --> 07:42.834
We've been through a lot, Aaron.
Not now, all right?

07:43.160 --> 07:48.394
I'm sorry, it's just that you're alive,
which is, you know, newsworthy.

07:49.040 --> 07:51.236
You knew about the necklaces
and the blackout.

07:51.400 --> 07:52.470
- Aaron.
AARON: Rachel.

07:52.640 --> 07:56.156
Ben gave me that necklace.
It drove me nuts. It almost got us all killed.

07:56.320 --> 07:58.072
- I deserve an explanation.
- We all do.

07:58.440 --> 08:02.832
I know. And I will explain everything,
all right?

08:03.240 --> 08:04.833
It's complicated.

08:05.040 --> 08:07.236
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

08:11.680 --> 08:12.829
Under the trees!

08:23.080 --> 08:24.832
Where are they going?

08:26.200 --> 08:28.350
West Chester's that way.

08:29.000 --> 08:31.276
There's a rebel camp in West Chester.

08:33.600 --> 08:37.514
Militia's moving rifles up here and here,
along I-76.

08:37.799 --> 08:39.871
If we hit hard and fast--

08:40.080 --> 08:42.116
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING NEARBY]

08:45.600 --> 08:46.749
Do you hear that?

08:56.560 --> 08:57.789
<i>Oh, my"</i>

09:54.120 --> 09:57.078
-ls anybody alive?
- No.

09:59.440 --> 10:02.000
I've never seen anything like this.

10:03.400 --> 10:06.279
This is what war used to look like
before the blackout.

10:07.960 --> 10:09.837
- Miles, I gotta go.
- Go where?

10:10.040 --> 10:12.031
- Central Command.
- What's Central Command?

10:12.200 --> 10:15.272
Rebel headquarters in Annapolis.
I gotta tell them about this.

10:15.640 --> 10:18.519
- I'm coming with you.
- Yeah. I am too.

10:18.720 --> 10:20.119
What? No. No way.

10:20.280 --> 10:22.874
They hit this, they hit the rest.
We have to warn them.

10:23.040 --> 10:25.429
I hung in there, okay?

10:25.640 --> 10:27.677
Through some very bad times.

10:28.280 --> 10:31.955
But we did it, we found Danny.
So, please, let's just go home.

10:33.480 --> 10:34.993
RACHEL:
What home?

10:35.360 --> 10:39.240
Sooner or later, Monroe will find us.
There's no home to go back to.

10:40.480 --> 10:44.713
- Then we leave the Monroe Republic.
- It's all going to be the Monroe Republic.

10:44.880 --> 10:47.235
- Rachel--
- I gave Monroe the amplifier.

10:47.400 --> 10:49.516
He has the helicopters because of me.

10:49.680 --> 10:51.796
All of this is because of me.

10:52.000 --> 10:54.560
- If it's not up to me to stop him then who?
MILES: Hey.

10:55.560 --> 10:56.709
But it's too late.

10:57.520 --> 11:00.512
How's anybody gonna win this?
With muskets and Crossbows?

11:00.720 --> 11:02.199
Then we get some bigger guns.

11:03.160 --> 11:04.753
Yeah. How?

11:07.360 --> 11:10.273
What if I was able to get the rebels
missile launchers?

11:10.480 --> 11:12.039
Thermal-guided. Surface to air.

11:16.960 --> 11:21.716
Rachel, firepower like that
takes imaging systems, tracking chips.

11:21.880 --> 11:23.632
It takes power.

11:25.280 --> 11:27.590
Monroe has power.

11:28.240 --> 11:30.550
Let's get some of our own.

11:32.000 --> 11:35.277
There's a guy I used to work with
not far from here. He can help us.

11:35.440 --> 11:38.592
AARON:
And this coworker of yours has electricity?

11:38.800 --> 11:42.316
Oh, I get it.
You can't explain and it's complicated.

11:45.000 --> 11:46.798
MILES:
You know I'm coming with you, right?

11:47.400 --> 11:49.960
Somebody's gotta keep you in one piece.

11:50.440 --> 11:52.511
And that's you?

11:53.440 --> 11:57.434
You're the one who's gonna make sure
that nothing bad happens to me?

11:58.880 --> 12:01.793
Well, it's not a discussion, Rachel.

12:02.640 --> 12:05.758
You guys see the choppers coming,
you run. You understand?

12:05.920 --> 12:07.797
Get out of sight.

12:11.480 --> 12:13.517
I'm proud of you.

12:13.840 --> 12:15.433
Both of you.

12:15.600 --> 12:16.954
I'll see you soon.

12:19.200 --> 12:22.955
Just come back this time, okay?

12:25.080 --> 12:26.957
I promise.

12:30.680 --> 12:32.512
It's okay.

12:32.680 --> 12:38.119
I'm gonna be here when you wake up.
I'm not going anywhere, I promise.

12:47.280 --> 12:49.191
I love you, Danny.

12:50.240 --> 12:55.269
I love you to the moon and back.

13:00.200 --> 13:01.873
I don't know.

13:02.320 --> 13:03.674
Maybe we shouldn't do this.

13:04.760 --> 13:08.754
No one's ever done this procedure before,
no one's even tested it.

13:09.240 --> 13:12.198
- He's not a science project.
BEN: You're right. He's our son.

13:12.960 --> 13:15.190
And nothing else has worked.

13:15.360 --> 13:17.317
This is what's left, okay?

13:33.400 --> 13:35.198
She'll be back.

13:49.000 --> 13:50.195
JASON:
That was a slaughter.

13:51.520 --> 13:55.354
I prefer "decisive."

13:58.160 --> 14:01.551
- There were families in there, sir.
- Which is a tragedy.

14:01.720 --> 14:05.679
But you tell me, what kind of enemy hides
behind their women and children?

14:25.120 --> 14:28.078
So let's have a little chat...

14:28.240 --> 14:31.119
...about where the closest rebel camp is.

14:50.800 --> 14:51.835
AARON:
Um, Nora?

14:52.000 --> 14:53.320
[GUNS COCK]

14:55.160 --> 14:59.279
I, uh, think we found your rebel base.

14:59.440 --> 15:01.158
[PEOPLE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

15:08.520 --> 15:10.909
I do not believe it.

15:11.560 --> 15:14.632
Nicholas. What are you doing here?

15:14.800 --> 15:17.030
Nora. You're a sight for sore eyes.

15:19.240 --> 15:21.038
- Charlie, right?
- Yeah.

15:23.040 --> 15:25.714
NICHOLAS: Meet Commander Ramsey.
- It's an honor, sir.

15:25.920 --> 15:27.718
I don't know about that.

15:27.880 --> 15:29.598
I'm not commander of much anymore.

15:29.760 --> 15:33.913
Yeah, and I was with the unit in Rockville
when they came and caught us by surprise.

15:34.080 --> 15:36.117
Never thought I'd see anything like that.

15:36.280 --> 15:38.749
- Saw them take out West Chester.
RAMSEY: Taking us all out.

15:38.920 --> 15:41.753
It's a full-on extermination.

15:42.000 --> 15:44.674
- So, what's the plan?
RAMSEY: Plan?

15:45.520 --> 15:49.036
This resistance, it's over for good.

15:51.800 --> 15:52.870
What if we can help?

15:54.680 --> 15:58.878
- And how are you gonna do that?
- We won't, Miles Matheson will.

16:11.160 --> 16:13.356
Are we ever gonna talk about...

16:14.000 --> 16:15.434
...you know...

16:16.000 --> 16:17.399
...this?

16:18.560 --> 16:20.631
There's nothing to talk about.

16:23.200 --> 16:25.396
Rachel, I saw a body.

16:26.960 --> 16:28.280
It was you.

16:32.440 --> 16:38.311
You gotta know
that I would never, ever have left...

16:38.480 --> 16:40.357
...if I thought you were alive.

16:47.520 --> 16:50.876
All this time with Bass...

16:54.280 --> 16:55.759
...he hurt you?

17:02.720 --> 17:04.118
<i>Hey-</i>

17:06.440 --> 17:08.271
Everything that happened...

17:11.119 --> 17:12.758
...it's all my fault.

17:13.160 --> 17:14.752
All of it.

17:17.599 --> 17:20.637
And I will never be able
to make it up to you.

17:22.720 --> 17:24.597
And I'm sorry.

17:38.480 --> 17:40.391
Step back.

17:42.760 --> 17:44.273
Please.

18:26.400 --> 18:28.437
Will you look at that?

18:30.760 --> 18:34.116
The Lord works in mysterious ways.

18:34.680 --> 18:36.114
Come on.

18:36.320 --> 18:38.436
Call in the air strike.

18:44.120 --> 18:46.077
Is there a problem?

18:47.000 --> 18:48.911
We can't do this.

18:50.240 --> 18:51.469
Excuse me?

18:52.000 --> 18:54.355
There are too many people in there.

18:55.240 --> 18:57.436
Is it really about the people?

18:57.600 --> 19:00.240
And not just one person in particular?

19:02.440 --> 19:05.512
That pert little bitch
has got you soft as a kitten.

19:05.680 --> 19:07.717
Need I remind you...

19:07.880 --> 19:09.712
...we are at war with these rebels.

19:09.880 --> 19:13.236
With those choppers, we're not fighting.

19:13.480 --> 19:15.312
We're butchering.

19:16.280 --> 19:18.317
I didn't sign on for this.

19:19.440 --> 19:23.877
You don't get to choose
what you sign on for.

19:24.040 --> 19:26.475
You follow orders.

19:28.440 --> 19:30.192
Not this time.

19:43.240 --> 19:44.275
Dad?

19:44.440 --> 19:46.192
[GRUNTS]

19:46.360 --> 19:49.671
You are a shameful disappointment to me.

19:51.000 --> 19:52.957
[YELLS]

19:57.440 --> 19:59.670
[BOTH GRUNTING]

20:16.920 --> 20:19.673
Don't ever come home again.

20:30.360 --> 20:31.475
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

20:34.680 --> 20:36.273
JOHN:
Rachel?

20:36.640 --> 20:38.551
Is that really you?

20:38.720 --> 20:41.872
Hey, John. It's been a long time.

20:42.040 --> 20:45.396
Yeah, yeah. Come in, come in.

20:52.520 --> 20:54.591
Where have you been?

20:54.760 --> 20:58.515
Philadelphia.
Monroe's been keeping me a prisoner.

20:58.680 --> 21:01.513
Well, why? Why, what happened?

21:04.120 --> 21:06.077
It's a long story.

21:07.320 --> 21:10.551
Um, who's he? Who are you?

21:10.720 --> 21:11.755
I'm a friend.

21:14.000 --> 21:16.037
Yeah?

21:17.120 --> 21:18.758
Okay.

21:18.960 --> 21:22.669
I'm just really glad to see you.
I thought for sure you were dead.

21:22.880 --> 21:26.191
- Have you spoken to anyone else?
- No, nobody. It's been radio silence.

21:26.560 --> 21:28.039
Really?

21:28.200 --> 21:31.079
- What about Grace?
- No. And she won't answer her computer.

21:31.240 --> 21:34.073
Nobody will.
You know, it's like they all just vanished.

21:34.240 --> 21:36.151
- Why?
- I don't know.

21:37.480 --> 21:38.709
Okay.

21:40.920 --> 21:44.038
John, we have other problems.
Monroe has an amplifier.

21:45.960 --> 21:47.439
What?

21:48.320 --> 21:49.390
How did he get it?

21:50.480 --> 21:51.515
From me.

21:53.800 --> 21:57.555
- From you?
- I made a mistake. I need to fix it.

21:58.280 --> 21:59.634
I need your help.

22:38.720 --> 22:40.791
JASON:
Charlie.

22:44.640 --> 22:46.631
I'm not gonna hurt you.

22:46.840 --> 22:49.912
You mean you're not gonna throw me
off a train again?

22:51.520 --> 22:52.635
Jason.

22:53.920 --> 22:55.752
- What?
- It's my real name.

22:56.360 --> 22:57.873
Jason Neville.

22:59.800 --> 23:02.519
Neville? Like Major Neville?

23:02.680 --> 23:03.875
He's my father.

23:04.720 --> 23:06.631
He spotted you and your camp.

23:06.800 --> 23:09.633
And now he's riding back
to give orders for an air strike.

23:09.800 --> 23:11.029
How long do we have?

23:11.760 --> 23:13.114
Twelve hours.

23:15.960 --> 23:18.110
You should get out of here.

23:18.440 --> 23:20.511
I don't have anywhere to go.

23:26.320 --> 23:28.470
Charlie, I'm finished...

23:28.640 --> 23:31.393
...With the Militia, With all of it.

23:32.880 --> 23:35.349
Look, I appreciate the warning...

23:35.960 --> 23:37.792
...but you can't come with me.

23:57.960 --> 24:00.634
Wait. You-- Be careful with that.

24:00.800 --> 24:01.835
What is it?

24:02.600 --> 24:04.796
It's a sonic canon.

24:05.000 --> 24:08.072
It emits a directional high-pitched
audio frequency.

24:08.240 --> 24:10.038
Knocks its targets out cold.

24:13.000 --> 24:17.870
And you just sit down here
with your necklace and your electricity...

24:18.040 --> 24:20.509
...just making stuff?

24:21.200 --> 24:23.555
It's a hobby. Yeah.

24:23.720 --> 24:26.553
I obviously have a lot of free time, so...

24:27.520 --> 24:29.352
Thank you.

24:31.160 --> 24:32.958
Oh! Sweet.

24:33.120 --> 24:35.999
Look at that. Yeah, we'll take one of these.

24:40.640 --> 24:42.358
You Okay?

24:42.520 --> 24:43.555
[SIGHS]

24:43.720 --> 24:46.360
Uh, no, Rachel.

24:46.520 --> 24:48.955
No, I'm not. I, uh...

24:49.920 --> 24:52.912
I have a confession to make about Grace.

24:53.720 --> 24:55.199
I do know what happened to her.

24:55.360 --> 24:57.397
I know why
she's not answering her computer.

24:58.680 --> 25:00.318
Why?

25:01.240 --> 25:03.038
Randall got to her.

25:05.160 --> 25:09.154
- Randall?
- And the thing is, Rachel, he got to me too.

25:09.360 --> 25:10.714
- No.
- I'm sorry.

25:11.160 --> 25:13.231
- John?
- I'm sorry.

25:13.400 --> 25:14.879
[HIGH-PITCHED WHINING]

25:15.040 --> 25:17.998
[RACHEL & MILES GRUNTING]

25:46.000 --> 25:47.991
RANDALL:
How's it all going?

25:48.160 --> 25:51.471
There's water damage, circuits are fried
and software's corrupted.

25:52.440 --> 25:55.432
- It's a rat's nest.
RANDALL: I have every confidence in you.

25:56.240 --> 25:57.878
Listen, something's come up.

25:59.040 --> 26:00.553
I've gotta take a little trip.

26:01.360 --> 26:04.478
But I leave you
in Mr. Austin's capable hands.

26:05.360 --> 26:06.634
You're leaving me with him?

26:08.160 --> 26:09.275
He's an animal.

26:09.920 --> 26:13.834
That's what makes him such an effective
and loyal associate...

26:14.000 --> 26:16.879
...ever since the DOD days.

26:18.920 --> 26:22.436
Just get the elevators working, Grace.
Get me down to Level 12.

26:26.440 --> 26:28.078
And if I can't?

26:35.840 --> 26:37.877
How much time
before the choppers get here?

26:38.040 --> 26:39.792
He said 12 hours.

26:39.960 --> 26:42.349
And we're sure this guy's legit?

26:42.520 --> 26:43.840
I don't see why he'd lie.

26:46.040 --> 26:47.678
Okay.

26:48.640 --> 26:50.597
They're coming at us with the big guns.

26:50.760 --> 26:53.991
We're not gonna be able to evacuate
all the wounded in time.

26:54.360 --> 26:55.873
So my vote...

26:57.600 --> 26:58.874
...we make our stand.

27:00.440 --> 27:03.671
- It's a long shot.
- Miles and Rachel will be here with missiles.

27:03.840 --> 27:07.151
- And if they're not?
- Then we use the guns we do have.

27:08.400 --> 27:11.756
I say we send a message to Monroe
that he can't do to us...

27:11.920 --> 27:14.799
...what the Russians, Germans,
or al Qaeda couldn't.

27:15.760 --> 27:17.478
And if we go down...

27:18.400 --> 27:20.038
...then we go down as Americans.

27:21.880 --> 27:23.393
I need volunteers.

27:23.560 --> 27:27.519
People to go out front, be the first line
of defense against the choppers.

27:48.560 --> 27:52.190
I'm sorry about this, Rachel. I really am.

27:52.680 --> 27:54.193
John...

27:54.960 --> 27:56.917
...listen to me.

27:57.520 --> 27:59.875
- You gotta let us go.
- No.

28:00.040 --> 28:03.032
No, I had to tell him you were here.
He's been looking for you.

28:03.240 --> 28:05.754
RACHEL: You mean Randall?
- Yes, I mean Randall.

28:07.280 --> 28:10.398
He's coming, Rachel. He'll be here soon.

28:11.160 --> 28:14.516
- He has big plans for you.
- John, my kids.

28:14.680 --> 28:17.240
- You can't do this.
- I don't have a choice.

28:17.400 --> 28:21.280
You know how dangerous Randall is.
You know how unbalanced he is.

28:21.440 --> 28:25.115
Which is exactly why I don't have a choice,
Rachel.

28:25.760 --> 28:27.876
Randall got into the tower.

28:30.520 --> 28:33.478
No. No, John, that's...

28:33.640 --> 28:36.200
I don't wanna hurt anybody.
He's making me help him...

28:36.400 --> 28:38.869
...and you know what will happen to me
if I don't.

28:39.040 --> 28:40.792
And if you don't help him...

28:41.800 --> 28:43.871
...you know what will happen to you too.

28:45.480 --> 28:47.232
[JOHN GRUNTING]

28:50.960 --> 28:52.519
- Hurry.
- Who the hell's Randall?

28:52.680 --> 28:57.038
Trust me, you don't wanna stay around
to find out. Let's get the weapons and go.

28:59.040 --> 29:00.997
And this Intel's accurate?

29:02.680 --> 29:03.750
Uh, yes, sir.

29:04.480 --> 29:07.916
I, uh, saw the Matheson girl myself.

29:09.480 --> 29:11.039
Did you see Miles with her?

29:11.200 --> 29:14.989
No. But we have to assume he's there,
don't we?

29:17.400 --> 29:18.674
I suppose so.

29:24.960 --> 29:27.839
- Order the strike.
MAN: Yes, sir.

29:30.840 --> 29:32.353
Thank you, Tom.

29:32.520 --> 29:35.353
You did good work out there.

29:38.200 --> 29:40.669
Are you all right? You seem a little rattled.

29:43.120 --> 29:44.190
It's my son.

29:47.000 --> 29:48.559
He's dead.

29:53.520 --> 29:55.352
I'm sorry.

30:01.760 --> 30:03.114
MAN:
Stack them right here.

30:06.320 --> 30:08.311
[MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

30:15.560 --> 30:17.551
[DAN NY GASPING]

30:19.360 --> 30:20.714
Danny? Danny.

30:21.240 --> 30:23.390
Danny, Danny. It's gonna be okay, all right?

30:23.560 --> 30:26.074
You're just having an asthma attack.
Calm down.

30:26.240 --> 30:28.754
It's gonna be okay.
Breathe the way I'm breathing.

30:34.320 --> 30:37.278
Just breathe, okay? Just breathe.

30:53.680 --> 30:56.115
- Hey.
- How you doing?

30:58.560 --> 31:00.278
Terrified.

31:01.760 --> 31:04.559
Well, don't worry.
Miles and Mom will be here soon.

31:07.160 --> 31:10.118
Danny, I gotta ask you for something.

31:11.880 --> 31:13.951
When the choppers come...

31:15.320 --> 31:17.118
...I need you to get inside.

31:18.520 --> 31:19.555
What?

31:19.720 --> 31:22.314
The medics are gonna need help
with the wounded.

31:22.880 --> 31:25.633
- I'm not hiding inside.
- Yes, you are.

31:25.800 --> 31:27.871
And you know why? Because you owe me.

31:30.080 --> 31:32.833
Because I walked over a thousand miles
to get to you.

31:33.000 --> 31:36.834
And I will never play this card again,
I'll never ask you for anything again...

31:37.040 --> 31:40.999
...but I'm asking you for this.
Please, sit this one out.

31:45.920 --> 31:50.630
Look, you're right, I could never repay you
for what you've done, but, Charlie...

31:52.840 --> 31:55.480
...it's not your job to look out for me
anymore.

31:57.080 --> 32:00.198
Charlie, I've gotta do this for Dad
and for Maggie...

32:00.360 --> 32:02.829
...and I've gotta do it for myself.

32:06.680 --> 32:08.671
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

32:16.720 --> 32:19.360
RAMSEY:
Positions! Get in positions! Go, go!

32:23.240 --> 32:25.470
MAN 1:
Come on.

32:25.640 --> 32:27.278
MAN 2:
All right, now!

32:31.400 --> 32:33.152
That's them on the left. I see them.

32:36.200 --> 32:38.999
All right, nobody fires!

32:39.160 --> 32:42.278
Nobody fires until I give the order!

33:11.400 --> 33:13.073
Fire!

33:28.840 --> 33:30.990
MAN:
Incoming!

33:41.880 --> 33:43.757
MAN:
Everyone down!

33:57.720 --> 33:59.631
RAMSEY:
Get him out of there!

34:03.480 --> 34:05.471
Regroup!

34:10.639 --> 34:11.869
RAMSEY:
Watch your side!

34:12.040 --> 34:13.599
Fire!

34:16.440 --> 34:17.635
Get down!

34:23.880 --> 34:24.915
I'm out.

34:52.280 --> 34:54.476
MILES:
All right, everybody stay down.

34:55.960 --> 34:57.030
[PENDANT POWERING UP]

34:57.480 --> 34:58.800
RACHEL:
Aim for that one.

34:58.960 --> 35:01.634
Amplifiers gotta be on that one.

35:34.080 --> 35:35.878
RACHEL:
Miles? Miles?

35:37.400 --> 35:38.834
Miles, wake up. Wake up.

35:39.280 --> 35:40.714
Wake up, Miles.

35:50.040 --> 35:51.360
Danny!

36:13.160 --> 36:15.436
We've lost power. We're going down.

36:42.160 --> 36:45.391
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

37:22.400 --> 37:25.677
<i>[I NAU DI</i> BLE]
<i>Breathe. Just breathe.</i>

37:56.200 --> 37:58.157
What...?

38:00.960 --> 38:03.031
What was I thinking?

38:04.520 --> 38:08.150
I never should have let you come here,
letyouu.

38:08.880 --> 38:10.757
...fight.

38:16.840 --> 38:19.275
I had you back.

38:26.040 --> 38:27.633
I'm...

38:28.280 --> 38:30.715
I'm his mother.

38:32.600 --> 38:35.831
I never should have let him out of my sight.

38:36.040 --> 38:37.678
.1111

38:41.280 --> 38:44.272
The two of you, you're...

38:44.840 --> 38:46.399
You're...

38:53.400 --> 38:55.710
There's nothing you could have done.

38:57.480 --> 39:00.871
Danny was set on this.
You couldn't stop him.

39:04.920 --> 39:09.232
So the only thing that matters now
is to finish what he started.

39:14.440 --> 39:16.829
We're going after Monroe.

39:18.840 --> 39:20.990
We're gonna help the rebels.

39:21.160 --> 39:24.755
We're gonna do whatever it takes
and we're gonna kill him.

39:25.800 --> 39:27.757
You and me.

39:28.680 --> 39:30.512
For Danny.

39:42.680 --> 39:44.239
Sir.

39:46.600 --> 39:47.954
I'm sorry to interrupt you.

39:48.320 --> 39:50.550
- There's a visitor.
- I'm not seeing anyone.

39:51.520 --> 39:53.397
I think you'll wanna see this one.

39:54.920 --> 39:56.558
Why?

39:57.960 --> 40:00.031
Because he drove here, sir.

40:02.040 --> 40:04.350
In a Cutlass Ciera.

40:11.040 --> 40:14.078
- How can I help you, Mr...?
RANDALL: Flynn.

40:14.240 --> 40:15.719
Randall Flynn.

40:15.880 --> 40:19.669
And this banged-up gentleman here
is John Sanborn.

40:19.840 --> 40:25.233
And the question, general,
is how can we help you?

40:45.760 --> 40:47.910
I love you, Danny.

40:48.720 --> 40:53.396
I love you to the moon and back.

42:48.640 --> 42:50.631
[English - US - SDH]
